#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:1
msgid "Changing colors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:7
msgid ""
"Furo allows customising colors to fit your brand's identity, by using CSS "
"variables. These can be declared directly in [`html_theme_options`][sphinx-"
"html_theme_options], in your `conf.py`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:9
msgid "How light and dark mode work"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:11
msgid ""
"Furo is in light mode by default, switching to the dark mode when requested "
"by the user's browser (through `prefers-color-scheme: dark`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:13
msgid ""
"As a consequence of this design, the dark mode inherits the variable "
"definitions from the light mode, only overriding specific values to adapt "
"the theme. While the mechanism for switching between light/dark mode is not "
"configurable, the exact CSS variable definitions used in this process can be "
"configured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:15
msgid ""
"It is possible to use different content for light and dark mode, by setting "
"`only-dark` and `only-light` classes on the content. This is the "
"[recommended approach](light-dark-images) for handling images with "
"backgrounds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:19
msgid "Using your own colors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:21
msgid ""
"Furo allows defining [CSS variables that overrides its default values](css-"
"variables). The exact variable names to use can be found in Furo's source "
"code [here](https://github.com/pradyunsg/furo/tree/main/src/furo/assets/"
"styles/variables)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:23
msgid ""
"This mechanism allows configuring nearly every facet of Furo's design, "
"including spacing between various items and the colors of nearly every "
"component."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:25
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:26
msgid ""
"Changing Furo's blue accent (used for stylising links, sidebar's content "
"etc) to a purple one:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:28
msgid ""
"html_theme_options = {\n"
"    \"light_css_variables\": {\n"
"        \"color-brand-primary\": \"#7C4DFF\",\n"
"        \"color-brand-content\": \"#7C4DFF\",\n"
"    },\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:38
msgid "Code block styling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:40
msgid ""
"Furo does not directly handle highlighting of the code blocks. This is done "
"by Sphinx, and is configurable using [`pygments_style`][sphinx-"
"pygments_style] and `pygments_dark_style` in `conf.py`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:42
msgid ""
"pygments_style = \"sphinx\"\n"
"pygments_dark_style = \"monokai\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../customisation/colors.md:48
msgid "`pygments_dark_style` is Furo-specific at this time."
msgstr ""
